body:
updating with information as requested by template (sorry, i just learned this existed. will report in this manner in the future).

### expected behaviour
as you scroll down the user list, all users should have "display name" showing as "last, first mi."

### actual behaviour
the first 30 ldap users show in the proper manner and then, starting with user 31, display name is populated with a string that looks similar to "c96882e3-58d5-xxxx-xxxx-fde9fe0e1b39" which is the content of the directory_uuid and owncloud_name according to entries oc_ldap_user_mapping.

### steps to reproduce
1. configure owncloud to authenticate to an ldap server that has more than 30 users
2. click on "users" button from the top-right drop down menu
3. scroll down past the 30th user

### server configuration
operating system: red hat enterprise linux server release 6.3 (santiago)

web server: httpd-2.2.15-26.el6.x86_64

database: mysql-server-5.1.67-1.el6_3.x86_64

php version: php-5.3.3-22.el6.x86_64

owncloud version: 5.0.0

### client configuration
browser: firefox 19, chrome 23, chrome 25

operating system: fedora 17, ubuntu 12.04, ubuntu 12.10, osx 10.8.3, windows 7

### logs
#### web server error log
web server has been logging in debug and has generated about 12gb of a log file over the last week. i can look for and provide specific information if requested but whole file is too large to upload.

